sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>Browser/kubectl
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    participant NBController as Notebook Controller<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Workbench<br/>StatefulSet Pod
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>HTTPS/443
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>REST API HTTPS/443
    participant Feast as Feast Feature Store<br/>gRPC/Online Store
    participant KServe as KServe Controller<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant ModelController as ODH Model Controller<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant Predictor as Model Predictor Pod<br/>HTTP/8080 mTLS
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>gRPC/8080
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.3
    participant Client as External Client<br/>Inference Requests
    participant DSPOp as DSP Operator<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant ArgoWorkflows as Argo Workflows<br/>Workflow Engine
    participant DataPrepPod as Data Prep Pod
    participant TrainingOp as Training Operator<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant TrainingPods as Training Pods<br/>Distributed
    participant TrainerV2 as Trainer v2<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant JobSet as JobSet Controller<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant LLMPods as LLM Training Pods<br/>DeepSpeed
    participant HuggingFace as HuggingFace Hub<br/>HTTPS/443
    participant LLMPredictor as vLLM Predictor<br/>LLM Inference

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over User,S3: Workflow 1: Model Development to Production
        User->>Dashboard: Access UI<br/>OAuth Bearer Token
        Dashboard->>NBController: Create Notebook CR<br/>kubectl apply
        NBController->>Notebook: Deploy StatefulSet<br/>Jupyter pod
        Notebook->>Feast: Read features<br/>gRPC feature serving
        Feast-->>Notebook: Feature vectors
        Notebook->>S3: Load training data<br/>AWS IAM credentials
        S3-->>Notebook: Dataset
        Note over Notebook: Train ML model<br/>(sklearn, PyTorch, TF)
        Notebook->>MLflow: Log experiment<br/>POST /api/2.0/mlflow/runs/log-metric
        Notebook->>ModelReg: Register model<br/>POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models
        ModelReg-->>Notebook: Model ID
        Notebook->>S3: Upload model artifacts<br/>PUT s3://bucket/models/
        User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService<br/>UI form
        Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>kubectl apply
        KServe->>Predictor: Deploy predictor<br/>Knative Service
        Predictor->>S3: Download model<br/>GET s3://bucket/models/
        S3-->>Predictor: Model artifacts
        KServe->>ModelController: Trigger Route creation<br/>Watch InferenceService
        ModelController->>Gateway: Create OpenShift Route<br/>External DNS
        KServe->>TrustyAI: Register for monitoring<br/>ServiceMonitor CR
    end

    rect rgb(255, 250, 240)
        Note over Client,Predictor: Workflow 2: Model Inference
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/mymodel:predict<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
        Gateway->>Predictor: Forward request<br/>mTLS STRICT
        Predictor->>Feast: Fetch real-time features<br/>gRPC
        Feast-->>Predictor: Features
        Note over Predictor: Run inference<br/>(vLLM, TensorFlow, Triton)
        Predictor-->>Gateway: Prediction result<br/>JSON response
        Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS response
        Predictor->>TrustyAI: Send inference metrics<br/>gRPC payload data
        TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Monitor fairness/drift<br/>SHAP explainability
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,S3: Workflow 3: Automated ML Pipeline
        User->>Dashboard: Submit pipeline<br/>DSP UI
        Dashboard->>DSPOp: Create DSPA CR
        DSPOp->>ArgoWorkflows: Create Workflow CR
        ArgoWorkflows->>DataPrepPod: Execute data prep step<br/>Pod
        DataPrepPod->>S3: Read/write data
        ArgoWorkflows->>TrainingOp: Create PyTorchJob CR
        TrainingOp->>TrainingPods: Deploy distributed training<br/>Multi-node pods
        TrainingPods->>S3: Load data & save checkpoints
        TrainingPods->>MLflow: Log metrics<br/>POST /api/2.0/mlflow/runs
        ArgoWorkflows->>ModelReg: Register model<br/>POST /api/model_registry
        ArgoWorkflows->>KServe: Deploy InferenceService<br/>kubectl apply
        KServe->>Predictor: Deploy model
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 250)
        Note over User,S3: Workflow 4: Distributed LLM Fine-tuning
        User->>Dashboard: Create TrainJob<br/>Trainer v2 CR
        Dashboard->>TrainerV2: kubectl apply TrainJob
        TrainerV2->>JobSet: Create JobSet CR<br/>Distributed pods
        JobSet->>LLMPods: Deploy training pods<br/>DeepSpeed/Megatron
        LLMPods->>HuggingFace: Download base LLM<br/>HTTPS/443
        HuggingFace-->>LLMPods: Model weights
        LLMPods->>S3: Load fine-tuning data
        S3-->>LLMPods: Training data
        Note over LLMPods: Distributed training<br/>Multi-GPU FSDP
        LLMPods->>S3: Save checkpoints<br/>PUT s3://bucket/
        LLMPods->>MLflow: Log training metrics
        LLMPods->>ModelReg: Register fine-tuned model
        User->>KServe: Deploy LLMInferenceService<br/>kubectl apply
        KServe->>LLMPredictor: Deploy vLLM predictor
        LLMPredictor->>S3: Load fine-tuned model
    end

    Note over User,Client: Legend:<br/>→ Solid: Primary flow<br/>--→ Dashed: Response/callback<br/>Protocols: HTTPS, gRPC, mTLS
